✅ Section 1: Work Impact
Provide 2–3 examples of how your work impacted the success of the company

Example 1: Strengthened Platform Reliability & Durability
I played a key role in improving the reliability and stability of our Kubernetes/EKS platforms across multiple environments.

Implemented node auto-repair mechanisms across dev, intg, accp, prod, and dr, ensuring higher uptime and reducing manual interventions during node failures.

Conducted memory consumption analysis that provided insights to optimize pod sizing and avoid performance degradation.
This work significantly enhanced operational resilience, reduced SLA risks, and ensured smooth customer experience during service transitions.

Example 2: Improved Observability & Performance for Better Decision Making
I implemented several observability-driven enhancements that directly strengthened system monitoring and performance optimization:

Built and deployed a new EKS Observability Dashboard behind Entra authentication, enabling secure and streamlined access.

Integrated Kentik across environments to provide deeper network and application performance insights.

Delivered an enhanced ACM certificate dashboard that reduced manual certificate tracking efforts.
These initiatives empowered teams with actionable visibility, improved responsiveness to incidents, and strengthened overall platform maturity.

Example 3: Accelerated Efficiency & Reduced Costs Across Environments
I contributed significantly to cost optimization and operational efficiency:

Proposed and implemented replica count adjustments based on actual CPU/memory consumption, saving unnecessary compute usage.

Led the Graviton LLD readiness plan to support future migration initiatives targeting cost and performance improvements.

Developed a unified end-to-end Jenkins orchestration pipeline that automates deployments for multiple environments, reducing developer effort and eliminating manual deployment errors.
These improvements directly contributed to lowering operational costs while improving deployment speed and developer productivity.

Example 4 (Optional): Security & Compliance Strengthening
To ensure the platform remains secure and compliant:

Enhanced existing vulnerability scanning Python processes and extended coverage to additional environments and workloads.

Worked with RedHat tools to strengthen container image security posture.
This work increased overall risk mitigation and reinforced security best practices across the organization.

✅ Section 2: Core Values Demonstration
Provide 2–3 examples of how you demonstrated core values while delivering the above impact

Excellence — Delivering High-Quality, Reliable Solutions
I demonstrated excellence by consistently delivering high-quality technical solutions such as EKS dashboards, node auto-repair, workload optimization, and observability enhancements.
I collaborated closely with cross-functional teams to ensure accuracy, alignment, and smooth deployment across all environments, often stepping in to resolve blockers proactively.

Customer-Driven — Proactive Support & Continuous Improvement
Throughout the year, I focused strongly on customer needs:

Built monitoring dashboards and automation that provide real-time visibility for internal and external customers.

Ensured seamless migrations and upgrades (Sybase-to-SQL readiness, EKS cluster upgrades, addon upgrades) with minimal disruption.

Delivered Decommissioning of legacy microservices (BAS-RITS-APP) to reduce customer-facing risk and simplify maintenance.
This ensured customers received consistent, stable, and predictable service quality.

Expertise — Applying Deep Technical Knowledge to Solve Complex Problems
I applied strong Kubernetes, AWS, observability, and automation expertise to:

Introduce modern tooling (Kentik, Kubecost POC, new EKS dashboards).

Guide teams during cluster upgrades and network monitoring improvements.

Evaluate alternative base images (Amazon Linux Tomcat POC) for better performance and cost efficiency.
This reinforced trust and credibility with stakeholders and helped teams adopt improved technical practices.

Agility — Adopting New Tools & Practices Quickly
I embraced new technologies proactively—Kentik, Kubecost, Graviton architectures, and Entra-integrated dashboards—to modernize operations.
I quickly adapted solutions across environments and iterated based on team feedback.
This agility allowed faster delivery of automation, dashboards, and security enhancements.

Compassion — Supporting Teams & Enabling Collaboration
I collaborated with teams during large-scale environment upgrades and helped resolve issues by being approachable, supportive, and solution-oriented.
I ensured knowledge sharing, documentation, and guidance so other teams could adopt new dashboards, pipelines, and monitoring tools easily.
This helped reduce workload stress and enabled a healthier team culture.

